{{Infobox FBI Ten Most Wanted | name = Genero Espinosa Dorantes | image = Genero Espinosa Dorantes.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Genero Espinosa Dorantes | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1970|6|19}} | birth_place = [[Pachuca]], [[Hidalgo (Mexico)|Hidalgo]], [[Mexico]] | birth_name = | death_date = | death_place = | cause = | nationality = | alias = | charge = Unlawful flight to avoid prosecution - Criminal homicide | conviction = | conviction_penalty = | conviction_status = | motive = | occupation = | spouse = | siblings = | parents = | children = | added_date = August 14, 2003 | caught_date = February 25, 2006 | remove_date = | number = 477 | status = Captured |Status choices: Caught Dead Removed |No status or other status defaults to currently on list }}
'''Genero Edgar Espinosa Dorantes''' (born June 19, 1970<ref name="DOC">{{cite web |url=http://www.tennesseeanytime.org/foil/search.jsp |title=Felony Offender Inmate Lookup |publisher=Tennessee Department of Correction |accessdate=March 7, 2010 }}</ref> in [[Pachuca]], [[Hidalgo (Mexico)|Hidalgo]], [[Mexico]]), is a Mexican criminal, who is the [[FBI Ten Most Wanted Fugitives, 2000s|477th fugitive listed]] on the [[FBI Ten Most Wanted Fugitives]] list.<ref>[https://www.fbi.gov/pressrel/pressrel03/dorantes081403.htm FBI National Press Release on Genero Espinosa Dorantes], August 14, 2003</ref>
He was wanted by the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] for his alleged participation in the burning, beating, torture and murder of his four-year-old stepson in [[Nashville, Tennessee]], in February 2003. He was considered armed and extremely dangerous. The FBI offered a reward of up to $100,000 for information leading directly to the arrest of Genero Espinosa Dorantes. On February 25, 2006, he was arrested in [[Tijuana]], [[Baja California]], [[Mexico]]. He was sentenced on July 8, 2006 and is currently incarcerated at the Northwest Correctional Complex, which is located in [[Tiptonville, Tennessee]]. He will be eligible for parole on December 12, 2064.<ref name="DOC"/>
